  "prompt": "Is romantic love real love?",
  "response": "Romantic love can be considered a form of real love, but it is one specific type among many different expressions of love. Romantic love often includes intense feelings of affection, attraction, and emotional connection toward another person. It typically involves desire and attachment that can lead to deep companionship and intimacy.\n\nHowever, love manifests in various ways beyond romantic relationships. For example, there is familial love, which is the deep bond and affection shared between family members; platonic love, which can exist between friends; and self-love, which involves caring for and valuing oneself. \n\nThe authenticity of love in any form generally hinges on qualities like mutual respect, trust, compassion, and commitment. Whether romantic love or other types, what matters most is the genuine connection and care shared between individuals.",
